.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-ABORT 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-abort \- restore the repository to pre-session state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch abort
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abort
undoes all changes made during the current session, including staged changes,
working-tree edits, commits, and batch mutations tracked by the session.
.PP
.B WARNING:
this can reset commits made during the session.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-stop (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-undo (1)
